# ComfyUI My Nodes

[![GitHub Stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/YOUR_USERNAME/ComfyUI-MyNodes?style=flat)](https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ComfyUI-MyNodes/stargazers)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE)
[![Python 3.10+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/)

Short one-line description of what your nodes do.

## Nodes

| Node | Description |
|---|---|
| **Load My Model** | Downloads and prepares the model configuration for inference. |
| **Example Image Node** | Processes an input image using the loaded model configuration. |
| **Save My Image** | Saves output images to the ComfyUI output folder. |

## Installation

### ComfyUI Manager

1. Open **ComfyUI Manager**
2. Search for `My Nodes`
3. Click **Install**
4. Restart ComfyUI

### Manual

```bash
cd ComfyUI/custom_nodes
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ComfyUI-MyNodes
```

Restart ComfyUI after installation. Dependencies install automatically on first run.

## Usage

1. Add **Load My Model** to your graph.
2. Choose `precision` and whether to enable `compile`.
3. Connect the `model_config` output to **Example Image Node**.
4. Feed an image into **Example Image Node**.
5. Adjust `strength`:
   `0.0` keeps the input unchanged, `1.0` is the default example behavior, and values above `1.0` amplify the effect.
6. Optionally connect **Save My Image** to write the result to disk.

The example node currently scales the input tensor and optionally composites with a mask.

## Requirements

- ComfyUI (recent version with V3 API support)
- Python 3.10+
- Any extra dependencies listed in [`requirements.txt`](requirements.txt)
- Optional GPU requirements specific to your real model

## Publishing

The included GitHub Actions workflow publishes on `v*` tags. Before using it, set `COMFY_API_KEY` in repository secrets and verify that your package metadata is final.

